{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0056-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Hob Recipes",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1739520000000,
  "modified": 1774988061086,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Quick-reference recipes for writing common items in "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0054-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Hob"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Each recipe shows the Hob code you'd put in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.hob"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (for views) or "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.code"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (for code items)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Three ways to write a view"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "There are three ways to define a view, depending on which item type and content field you use:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Approach"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Item type"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Content field"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "You write"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Kernel does"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "Hob view"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "view"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "content.hob"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Just the render expression"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Wraps it in a function, injects "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "item"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " and "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " into scope"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "JS view"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "view"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "content.code"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Full ES module with "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "export async function render(item, api)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Loads as module, calls "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": ".render()"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "def-view"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "code"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "content.code"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Hob code using "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "def-view"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " macro"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Reads "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": ":for-type"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " and "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": ":render"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " from the exported map"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A Hob view is the most concise — the kernel already knows it's a view (from the item type) so the code is just the body of the render function. A JS view is a full module that must export its own "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "render"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". The "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "def-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " macro is for when you want a Hob view inside a code item (where the item type is "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "code"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", not "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", so you need to explicitly declare the type binding)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "View (Hob)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Put the Hob expression in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.hob"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on a view item (type "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). The kernel wraps this into a render function and injects "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — just write the expression that returns hiccup."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; Simple note view — shows title + body\n(let [note (get-item (:id item))]\n  [:div {:style \"padding: 16px;\"}\n    [:h1 (:name note)]\n    [:div {:style \"white-space: pre-wrap;\"}\n      (or (get-in note [:content :description]) \"(empty)\")]])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Call "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " during render to register the item as a reactivity dependency — the view auto-refreshes when it changes."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "View with tags"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(let [note (get-item (:id item))\n      tags (or (get-in note [:content :tags]) [])]\n  [:div {:style \"padding: 16px;\"}\n    [:h2 (:name note)]\n    (when (seq tags)\n      [:div {:style \"display: flex; gap: 4px; margin-bottom: 8px;\"}\n        (for [tag-id tags]\n          (let [tag (get-item tag-id)]\n            [:span {:style \"background: #e0e0e0; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.8em;\"}\n              (:name tag)]))])\n    [:div (or (get-in note [:content :description]) \"(empty)\")]])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "View with click handlers"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(let [note (get-item (:id item))\n      counter (atom 0)]\n  [:div {:style \"padding: 16px;\"}\n    [:h2 (:name note)]\n    [:button {:on-click (fn [e] (swap! counter inc))}\n      (str \"Clicked \" (deref counter) \" times\")]])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "View with conditional rendering"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(let [note (get-item (:id item))\n      body (get-in note [:content :description])]\n  [:div {:style \"padding: 16px;\"}\n    [:h2 (:name note)]\n    (if body\n      [:div {:style \"white-space: pre-wrap;\"} body]\n      [:p {:style \"color: #999; font-style: italic;\"} \"No content yet.\"])])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "View with child items"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(let [note (get-item (:id item))\n      children (:attachments note)]\n  [:div {:style \"padding: 16px;\"}\n    [:h2 (:name note)]\n    (when (seq children)\n      [:div {:style \"margin-top: 12px;\"}\n        (for [child-id children]\n          (render-item child-id))])])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "render-item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " returns a DOM element for the child, rendered with its own best-matching view."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "View (def-view macro)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Use "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "def-view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " when writing a view inside a code item (type "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "code"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). Since the item type is "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "code"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " rather than "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "view"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", the kernel won't automatically treat it as a view — the macro explicitly declares the type binding and render function:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(def-view my-note-view @note-type [item api]\n  [:div.note\n    [:h2 (:name item)]\n    [:p (.. item :content :description)]])"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This expands to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(def my-note-view {:for-type @note-type :render (fn [item api] ...)})"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". The kernel reads "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":for-type"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":render"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " from the resulting map to register the view."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Watch"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A watch reacts to events. Use the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "def-watch"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " macro:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; Log when any note is updated\n(def-watch note-logger {:event :item/updated :type @note-type} [event api]\n  (log (str \"Note changed: \" (.. (:item event) :name))))"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Watch with type-extends filter"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; React to changes on items whose type chain includes @note-type\n(def-watch note-chain-watcher {:event :item/updated :type-extends @note-type} [event api]\n  (let [item (:item event)\n        prev (:previous event)]\n    (when (not= (.. item :content :title) (.. prev :content :title))\n      (log \"Title changed!\"))))"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Watch that emits another event"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(def-watch tag-counter {:event :item/updated :type @note-type} [event api]\n  (let [tags (or (.. (:item event) :content :tags) [])]\n    (emit! {:type \"tag-count-changed\" :content {:count (count tags)}})))"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Library"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A library exports reusable functions. Other items load it with "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(require lib-name)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; Library: string-helpers\n(defn truncate [s max-len]\n  (if (<= (count s) max-len)\n    s\n    (str (subs s 0 (- max-len 3)) \"...\")))\n\n(defn slug [s]\n  (-> s\n    str/lower-case\n    (str/replace \" \" \"-\")))\n\n(export truncate slug)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Consumers:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(require string-helpers)\n(string-helpers/truncate \"A very long title\" 20)\n\n;; or destructured:\n(require [truncate slug] from string-helpers)\n(truncate \"Hello world\" 8)  ;; => \"Hello...\""
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Event handler function"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A plain function that handles an event — typically referenced from a watch or called directly:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(defn on-kernel-boot-complete [event api]\n  (log \"System booted!\"))"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Handler names follow the convention "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "on-{event-name}"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " with kebab-case."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Hiccup quick reference"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Pattern"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Result"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "[:div \"text\"]"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "<div>text</div>"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "[:div.my-class \"text\"]"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "<div class=\"my-class\">text</div>"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "[:div#main \"text\"]"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "<div id=\"main\">text</div>"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "[:div {:style \"color: red;\"} \"text\"]"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "<div style=\"color: red;\">text</div>"
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "[:input {:type \"text\" :value v :on-input handler}]"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "<input>"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " with handler"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(for [x items] [:li x])"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "list of "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "<li>"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " elements"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(when cond [:div \"shown\"])"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "conditional element (nil = omitted)"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(render-item id)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "embedded child view"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "View operations"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "These functions are available inside view render contexts:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Function"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Effect"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(open-item! e id)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Open item contextually with modifier key support (Ctrl/Cmd=new tab, Alt=root, plain=attach to parent)"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(navigate! id)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Navigate to item as root (always replaces the current root)"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(render-item id)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Render a child item inline, returns DOM"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "(rerender!)"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Force the current view to re-render"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Use "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "open-item!"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for click-to-open interactions — pass the event "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "e"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " so modifier keys work. Use "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "navigate!"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " only when you specifically want root navigation regardless of context."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; Clickable card — plain click attaches, Ctrl/Cmd opens new tab, Alt opens as root\n[:div {:on-click (fn [e] (open-item! e (:id it)))} (:name it)]"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "@"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " vs "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — when to use which"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Both fetch an item and register a reactivity dependency, but they serve different purposes:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`@name` / `@uuid`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — reference a "
            },
            [
              ":em",
              {
                "s": "known"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " item by name or ID. Use this for types, tags, and other well-known items whose identity you know at write time: "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@note-type"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@my-tag"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`(get-item id)`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — fetch an item by a "
            },
            [
              ":em",
              {
                "s": "runtime"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " variable. Use this inside views to re-fetch the current item being rendered, since the view parameter "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "item"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " is a plain object that doesn't register reactivity. Calling "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(get-item (:id item))"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " tells the dependency tracker \"this view depends on this item\" so it auto-refreshes on changes."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Rule of thumb: if you can name it, use "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "@"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". If the ID comes from a variable (the view's "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", a loop, a query result), use "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Item reference cheat sheet"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Syntax"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Meaning"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "@my-item"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Reference a known item by name (tracked)"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "@a1b2c3d4-..."
                }
